Direct Known Subclasses:
Acronym, AcronymExpansion, Organization, PersonalName, Shape
public class LexicalElement
extends VAnnotation
Lexical Element is a container class for the terms of a document. A term is a word or words that equate to what you'd find in a dictionary. This includes both single and multi-token items such as "a priori". This class also includes multiple tokens that wouldn't be covered in a dictionary like dates, times, phone numbers, urls, and identifiers. Updated by JCasGen Wed Aug 17 13:31:49 EDT 2022 XML source: C:/Users/divitag2/work/softwareRepos/bodyFunction/project/60_03_type-descriptors/target/jcasgen/typesystem.xml
